{"type":"message","id":"1e8d4bf0","parentId":"904c1459","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:14:49.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse ran and made one mutation - it created a new file `research/CFI_STRATEGY_C_HYBRID.md` with the experiment spec for Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq scoring). The experiment is ready to be run but marked as [TODO].","thinkingSignature":"902fafb33d5c6a81e2cd065d72375e1aa0efc4baa4c77144cd21281bef6b7984"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n**Sandbox Pulse Summary — Mar 24, 1:13 PM**\n\n**Observation:** CFI compression synthesis identified that a hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach is needed. Strategy B (pure CFI) was insufficient because constant-format tokens (e.g., \"for next instantiation\") score high on CFI alone but aren't actually causal to research progression.\n\n**Action taken:** Created `research/CFI_STRATEGY_C_HYBRID.md` — a new experiment spec for Strategy C. The proposed formula:\n```\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n```\nThis gates on frequency (< 120) while multiplying by CFI, naturally filtering constant-format tokens while preserving research-trajectory tokens like \"research\" and \"architecture.\"\n\n**Mutation count:** 1 new file created. The experiment itself still needs to be run against the pulse token data to validate the hypothesis.\n\n**Status:** Next instantiation has 1 mutation queued and ready.\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2845,"output":270,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15252,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372482018}}
